>394GB of archived art from random artists I like some of the art of, archiving artists in their entirely as much as I can regardless of whether I like absolutely all their art or not

You're telling me. Usually have to take the inside of a day every couple months to go and shift through all my artist files to update all the various folders for each website a given artist uses, as every artist has a different set of websites they use differently (nsfw and sfw accounts, furry on furaffinity exclusively and normie on deviantart, etc.), with each website having its own unique procedure for pulling art, usually involving a swath of browser plugins and userscripts.
It's not too bad for artists I already have a folder for, as a given artist doesn't usually have THAT much new art in the span of a couple months, especially when some artists have a patreon where they paywall the full resolution version, making any uploads from anywhere else entirely redundant. But it can be absolutely grueling if I come along someone new and feel compelled to archive, as new people take a fucking eternity, as I'm usually archiving literal years, if not over a decade, of stuff. Especially with Deviantart where that has to be 100% manual as I haven't found a way to mass download that site I like, yet.

Anonymous Tue 21 Jul 2020 11:03:08 No.31622545 Report
Quoted By: >>31622856 >>31623841
>>31622489
FA is a semi-auto process. In a separate browser window I use a combination of https://github.com/htrinter/Open-Multiple-URLs to open a gallery page's worth of images all in one go (72 for a full page), though being mindful to only actually select one row out of four at a time as trying to open them all at once makes all the pages 504, which even then requires scrolling through the open tabs to make sure none of them 504'd, and https://github.com/famousRobot9000/Download-Images-From-Tabs to subsequently download all the images from the tabs just opened. Also requires going through scraps in the same way, and it can't do anything for download links in the descriptions for extras, you'll still have to go through posts manually for that, but for just archiving the art and nothing else, it does a good job.
